text.section:
"Slave" means an individual:
who had no freedom of action;
whose person and services were wholly under the control of another;
who was in a state of enforced compulsory service to another; and
who could not legally leave enforced compulsory service to another on the individual's own initiative during the individual's lifetime before the end of the slavery era.

"Slaveholder" means:
an owner of a slave;
an owner of a commercial enterprise that used the services of a slave;
an owner of a vessel or other means of transporting slaves; or
a person dealing in the purchase, sale, or financing of the business of slaves and slavery.
